<SLUG> BC-China-Tibet-Earthquakes </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Tibet rattled by pair of earthquakes: report
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BEIJING (AP) _ Two earthquakes, with magnitudes of 5.1 and 5.3,
hit Xanza county in Tibet Saturday evening, but there were no
reports of casualties, China's state-run Xinhua News Agency
reported Sunday.
	   The quakes struck northwest of Lhasa, capital of the region, at
7:06 p.m. (1106 GMT) and 7:13 p.m. (1113 GMT) Saturday.
	   The Chinese Central Seismology Bureau on Sunday said it had not
received reports of injuries or damage.
 &UR; (rs) 	   
