<SLUG> BC-Russia-NKorea-Boy </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Body believed to to be missing son of North Korean diplomat found
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Police said the body of a child found in a stream
was believed to be the missing son of a North Korean diplomat,
according to a news report Sunday.
	   Police said they were still conducting tests, but initial
evidence indicated it was the body of the two-year-old child who
went missing May 30 while on an outing with his father and other
diplomats from the North Korean embassy.
	   The child went missing in a park just 100 meters (yards) from
the North Korean embassy in central Moscow. The body was found in a
stream in the west of the city.
	   (ren)
</TEXT>
