<HEADLINE>
BALTIMORE: Orlando Palmeiro.
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   In St. Louis, Bill Mueller ended another marathon between the
Giants and the Cardinals with a 14th-inning RBI single for a 5-4
victory Saturday night to extended San Francisco's winning streak
to eight games.
	   Brent Mayne walked off Sean Lowe (0-2) to start the 14th and
advanced on a sacrifice. Darryl Hamilton also walked before
Mueller, who was 2-for-7, dumped a single into shallow center that
scored Mayne.
	   Rich Rodriguez (1-0), San Francisco's seventh pitcher, worked
three scoreless innings as the Giants moved into first place in the
NL West, a game ahead of San Diego.
	   The five-hour, nine-minute game was the third extra-inning
contest in nine meetings between the teams, with previous marathons
of 17 and 12 innings.
	   Mark McGwire, who hit his major league-leading 28th home run on
Friday, went 0-for-3 with three intentional walks.
