<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Golf-Resorttrust Ladies </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Harada wins Resorttrust Ladies
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KITA, Japan (AP) _ Overnight co-leader Kaori Harada won her
second title of the season Sunday, clinching a two-stroke victory
in the Resorttrust Ladies with a final round of 2-under-par 70.
	   Harada, winner of the Glory Queens in April, shot four birdies
and two bogeys for a 9-under 207 total, two shots ahead of Natsuko
Noro.
	   Harada's seventh career victory was worth 9 million yen (dlrs
65,000) from a purse of 50 million yen (dlrs 362,000).
	   ``I thought of winning when I learned I was leading by two
strokes after the 16th,'' said Harada. ``But I tried to stay
persistent in order not to make a goof for the second straight
week.''
	   She was referring to her final round of 70 to finish second in
the Toto Motor Ladies last week. South Korean Lee Young-me, one of
Harada's two overnight co-leaders, won that tournament with a final
round of 69.
	   On Sunday, Natsuko Noro, in contention for her second career
victory, shot a 70 for 209.
	   Yuri Fudo fired the day's best round of 68 and shared third at
210 with Taiwan's Tseng Hsiu-feng, who shot a 71.
	   Akiko Fukushima, the other co-leader overnight, had a fat 74 for
a share of fifth at 211 with Fumiko Muraguchi, who shot a 69.
	   Fukushima, the 1996 and 1997 money earnings leader, has yet to
win this season. 	   
</TEXT>
