<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Russia-Explosion </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Homemade bomb injures guard near Chechnya
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ A homemade bomb exploded outside a border guard
checkpoint in southern Russia, damaging the building and injuring
one officer, the ITAR-Tass news agency reported.
	   The incident occurred late Saturday in Nazran, a city in the
restive region of Ingushetia, which borders the rebel republic of
Chechnya, the report said.
	   One guard was slightly injured by flying plaster, ITAR-Tass
said.
	   Although Russia's war with Chechnya ended nearly two years ago,
the area remains troubled by violence.
	   (mr)
</TEXT>
