<HEADLINE>
Mandela to attend CARICOM meeting in St. Lucia
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) _ President Nelson Mandela will
attend a meeting of Caribbean heads of state from June 30-July 4,
the foreign ministry annnounced Sunday.
	   The chairman of the Caribbean Community and Common Market and
Prime Minister of Grenada, Keith Mitchell, had invited Mandela,
according to the foreign ministry.
	   The statement said Mandela would emphasise the importance of
South Africa's growing relations with the Caribbean community
during his visit.
	   South African exports to the Caribbean region in 1997 reached
425 million rand (dlrs 83 million), more than double the figure for
1996. Total imports from the region increased to 112 million rand
(dlrs 21 million).
