<SLUG> BC-Israel-Teacher Strike </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Nationwide strike by teachers shuts most schools
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   JERUSALEM (AP) _ A nationwide strike by Israel's teachers to
protest changes in their pension plans and the firing of some
colleagues shut down most on the country's schools on Sunday.
	   The one-day strike by teachers belonging to the Histadrut labor
federation affected 1 million students, from kindergarteners to
college students.
	   Non-unionized teachers held a few classes, however. Sundays are
regular school days in Israel.
	   In December, a nationwide strike by public employees, including
teachers, paralyzed much of Israel for five days.
