<HEADLINE>
Bomb rips through train killing 26 people
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: RAISES death toll from 20 to 26, increases number injured from
25 to 45. ADDs photo numbers &QL; 
 &UR; AP Photos KAR101, LAR101-102 &QL; 
 &UR; By ZAHID HUSSAIN &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   KARACHI, Pakistan (AP) _ A powerful bomb gutted a train
traveling through southern Pakistan on Sunday, killing 26 people
and wounding 45 others, many of them seriously, police and
emergency workers said.
	   The bomb exploded just before dawn, shattering the train as it
passed through a village 30 kilometers (18 miles) outside Sukkur
and 200 kilometers (120 miles) north of Karachi, capital of the
southern Sindh province, police said.
	   The 18-carriage express, with a capacity of 1,800 passengers,
was headed toward the northwestern city of Peshawar, they said.
Among the dead were four children aged 5 or younger, police said.
