event.
 &UR; MAIN SPOT NEWS:
	   ASMARA, Eritrea _ With a border dispute escalating into bombing
raids, hundreds of foreigners scramble out of Eritrea, fearing it
will be engulfed in war with Ethiopia. ERITREA-ETHIOPIA. Lead has
moved. By Karin Davies.
	   UNITED NATIONS _ The 15 members of the Security Council have
demanded, in a unanimous vote, that India and Pakistan refrain from
further nuclear tests, halt weapons programs and sign nuclear
control agreements unconditionally. UN-INDIA-PAKISTAN. Recap has
moved. By Robert H. Reid.
	   PRISTINA, Yugoslavia _ The Kosovo Liberation Army appeals Sunday
to fellow ethnic Albanians to help the rebel cause, urging them to
join the fight for freedom from Serbia. YUGOSLAVIA-KOSOVO. Expected
by 1300 GMT. By Ismet Hajdari.
	   BAGHDAD, Iraq _ Iraq will turn down future humanitarian aid, and
Saddam Hussein asks donors instead to lobby to lift trade
sanctions. IRAQ-AID. Has moved to some points; Expected to others
by 1200 GMT. By Leon Barkho.
	   PARIS _ With the World Cup four days away, both sides in a
strike by Air France pilots appeared willing Sunday to begin new
talks aimed at ending the walkout now in its seventh day. AIR
FRANCE-STRIKE. Lead has moved. By Deborah Seward.
	   FAISABAD, Afghanistan _ Aid workers are on the lookout for
serious disease in the earthquake-ravaged regions of northern
Afghanistan. AFGHANISTAN-QUAKE. Expected by 1000 GMT. By Judith
Ingram. AP Photos FBD101-103.
