<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Police divers have recovered the body of a
2-year-old boy identified as the missing son of a North Korean
diplomat, a news agency said Sunday.
	   Police said the father has identified the body, which was found
on Saturday in a small tributary to the Moscow River, the ITAR-Tass
news agency said. The site was about 2 kilometers (more than a
mile) downstream from where the toddler disappeared May 30 while on
an outing with his father and other diplomats from the North Korean
embassy.
	   Police are investigating the case, but believe it was an
accident, the report said.
