<HEADLINE>
Hong Kong edges Japan 17-16 in Pacific Rim rugby
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TOKYO (AP) _ Hong Kong edged Japan 17-16 Sunday for a 3-1 record
in the four-nation Pacific Rim rugby championship. Japan fell to
1-3.
	   At Tokyo's Prince Chichibu Memorial Ground, Japan led 13-10 at
halftime after stand-off Stephan Miln's penalty goal and a try by
No. 8 Ross Tompson helped it overcome the visitors' four-point
lead.
	   After the break, however, Hong Kong regained its lead with a try
by scrum-half Sean O'Hara.
	   Japan, currently in third place, will meet the United States in
San Francisco Saturday.
	   Hong Kong, front-running in the home-and-away round-robin
tournament, will visit Canada on the same day. 	   
