	   He also said he hoped that a U.N. conference on fighting drugs
opening Monday would give a ``new and concrete impulse'' toward
cooperation on the issue.
	   Drug trafficking, production and use ``constitute a market of
death, which corrodes and weakens the human being,'' he said.
