<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Tunisia-England,0307 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
World Cup: Tunisia is ``ready'' for England
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TUNIS, Tunisia (AP) _ Forget that underdog stuff. After routing
Wales in a World Cup warmup, Tunisia says it wants England.
	   ``We are ready for you,'' Tunisia's Polish coach Henry
Kasperczak said after reflecting on Saturday's 4-0 victory in
Tunis. ``We are fit and ready, the side is knitting together well
and with a week or so to go before the game, I am happy with the
preparations.''
	   Tunisia plays England in the opening match for both teams in
Marseille on June 15, so the exhibition match essentially was an
effort by non-qualifier Wales to help out its neighbor by doing a
little scouting.
	   ``England will win in Marseille, I am sure of that,'' Welsh
striker John Hartson added. ``They will be too strong for Tunisia.
To be fair, we made them look good, it was so hot out there and
after all the traveling we have done and at the end of a long
season for a lot of our lads it was a game too far for us.''
	   But Wales manager Bobby Gould warns that England should be wary
of 25-year-old sweeper Khaled Badra, who scored one goal from 35
yards. Gould said Badra could step straight into the English
Premier League.
	   ``He carried the ball out of defense well. He is strong and
confident on the ball,'' Gould said. ``After witnessing his
performance against us, my advice to England is not to let him get
into range with shooting like that.''
	   That's the kind of talk Kasperczak likes to hear.
	   ``I believe good players will win matches in France and we want
to prove we have good players,'' Kasperczak said. ``We know the
quality of English football, but the important thing now is that
they think ahead and think what we are capable of. We hope they are
now a little worried.''
</TEXT>
