<SLUG> BC-Ukraine-Radioactive </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Ukrainian authorities release plane with radioactive cargo
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KIEV, Ukraine (AP) _ Ukrainian customs officials have released a
Kazak plane carrying more than 40 tons of metal drums emitting
radioactivity, a customs official said Sunday.
	   The containers were filled with radioactive waste apparently
intended for burial, said Pavel Busyhin, duty customs officer in
the western Ukrainian town of Rivne.
	   An inspection of the plane found all papers to be in ``proper
order,'' he told the Interfax news agency.
	   The Kazakstani Il-76 was detained when it made a refueling stop
in Rivne Saturday. It had been en route to Russia from Germany.
	   The report did not clarify the radioactive waste's origin.
