<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Tennis-French Open-Men's Running </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Moya leads in men's final
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   PARIS (AP) _ Carlos Moya took the lead over Alex Corretja Sunday
in the men's final of the French Open, winning the first set, 6-3.
	   Moya had a relatively easy time breaking Corretja in the first
game, and again in the seventh.
	   The windy conditions eliminated chances for the long rallies for
which the Spaniards are known. Misplays on serves and volleys
caused both men trouble.
	   Whoever wins, Spaniards will have swept both singles events at
the French Open.
	   Arantxa Sanchez Vicario won the women's title Saturday, beating
Monica Seles.
	   Spanish men have won the French Open five times previously, but
have only taken three other Grand Slam titles.
	   Moya already has a major clay court title this year, at Monte
Carlo. Corretja lost to Moya there and in the final of another top
clay court tournament in Hamburg.
	   Moya, seeded 12th, is 28-12 this year. Corretja, seeded 14th,
took a 27-8 record into the final.
	   (sz-jn) 	   
