<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Italy-Parliament Fire, 1st Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Small fire extinguished at Italian Parliament building
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: ADDS description of damage, fire discovered by guard; no
pickup &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   ROME (AP) _ A small blaze broke out in an office of the Chamber
of Deputies building Sunday but was quickly extinguished, officials
said.
	   A short-circuit involving an air-conditioner caused the fire,
which was fed by papers in the small room on the fifth floor
according to Danilo Bellini supervisor of the fire department's
operations room.
	   The fire caused much smoke, but no injuries or evacuations were
reported, he said. The room was heavily damaged, firefighters said.
	   A guard on hourly patrol smelled something burning and saw
smoke, and sounded the alarm, they said.
	   The Montecitorio Palace, designed in 1650 by Gianlorenzo
Bernini, has been the seat of the chamber since 1871. The chamber
is the lower house of Parliament, which includes the Senate.
	   (cr/djw)
</TEXT>
