w1487 &Cx1f; wstm-
r i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-GuineaBissau-fighting     06-07 0184
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Guinea Bissau-fighting,0183 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Report: Troops exchange gunfire, 10 killed, in Guinea Bissau
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LISBON, Portugal (AP) - Soldiers exchanged gunfire early Sunday
in the capital of Guinea Bissau, in West Africa, killing up to 10
people, news reports said.
	   Shooting started at 0530 GMT at the military headquarters in
Bissau and lasted for more than three hours, the Portuguese news
agency Lusa reported.
	   The ten people killed were soldiers, the agency reported.
	   Lusa said the clash may have been triggered by changes in the
military hierarchy last Friday.
	   Guinea's Defense Minister Samba Lamine Mane said in a statement
that troops loyal to the government had brought the situation under
control, Lusa said.
	   An official announcement in Bissau urged people to stay off the
streets.
	   The Portuguese ambassador to Bissau, Francisco Henriques da
Silva, speaking on Lisbon radio TSF, said that calm had returned to
the capital by mid-morning.
	   Guinea-Bissau, a former Portuguese colony with a population of
nearly a million people, borders Senegal and Guinea-Conakry. 	   
</TEXT>
