<HEADLINE>
Yeltsin, Kohl to meet for broad-ranging talks
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BONN, Germany (AP) _ In his first trip abroad since Russia's
financial crisis, Russian President Boris Yeltsin arrives Monday to
discuss political, financial, trade and social issues with German
Chancellor Helmut Kohl.
	   A German government official said Russia's relations with
neighboring Ukraine, the European Union and the NATO military
alliance also would be on the agenda.
	   Yeltsin and his top officials insist their country has rebounded
from last month's collapse in Russian markets, and that they don't
need handouts. However, they have stressed that foreign credit
remains crucial for Russia.
	   Still, investors have said they believe a bailout package may be
unveiled Tuesday, when deputy finance ministers from Germany and
the other Group of Eight economic powers meet in Paris.
	   The German officials said Germany was prepared to plead Russia's
case with the International Monetary Fund, but that there would be
no direct German aid.
	   Yeltsin also is to have breakfast Tuesday morning with
opposition chancellor candidate Gerhard Schroeder. He returns to
Moscow on Tuesday.
	   (im/cb)
