<SLUG> BC-Greece-Sailors Killed </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Ukrainian sailors killed in maintenance accident
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ATHENS, Greece (AP) _ Two Ukrainian sailors were killed Sunday
in an accident which occurred during maintenance work on their
ship, anchored off the coast of the northern Greek port of
Igoumenitsa, media reports said.
	   Anatoly Chykhry, the 57-year-old captain of the Ukranian-flagged
dredger ship Zakharyan, and boatswain Leonid Mataidora, 32, were
killed during work on the ship's digging system, reports said. No
further details of the accident were immediately available.
	   Another two of the ship's sailors, whose names were not
released, were treated for minor injuries in Igoumenitsa hospital.
	   The Zakharyan, with a crew of 35 Ukrainian sailors, had been
anchored off the coast of Igoumenitsa for maintenance work since
last Monday.
	   Port authorities are investigating the cause of the accident.
	   (eb)	   
</TEXT>
