<HEADLINE>
'Surya' apologizes for mistake, JAKARTA POST
</HEADLINE>
'Surya' apologizes for mistake, JAKARTA POST &QL; 
   June 06, 1998
   JAKARTA POST
   INDONESIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   SURABAYA: The East Java-based Surya daily admitted yesterday
that it had made a mistake in a report which said that opposition
figure Amien Rais was among those earmarked to receive a total of
Rp 260 billion (US$22.6 million) for helping to topple former
president Soeharto.
	   Deputy chief editor Basuki Subianto conceded that his reporters
had made a mistake when they failed to recheck an item found on the
Internet which claimed the New York Times had written that Amien
Rais had received the money.
	   About 200 students from a Muhammadiyah youth group rallied in
front of the daily's office to protest the article.
	   One of the student representatives pointed out in a meeting with
Surya editorial staff that the original New York Times article of
May 20 never mentioned Amien Rais as a recipient.
	   Basuki formally apologized for the mistake and agreed to a set
of corrective measures including printing a half-page apology.
	   The daily also said it would print a special interview with
Amien Rais explaining the matter and would also place quarter page
apologies in the Jawa Pos and Surabaya Pos dailies. (nur)
	   
</TEXT>
