<HEADLINE>
Russian defense minister to visit Belgium
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Russian Defense Minister Igor Sergeyev travels to
Belgium Monday for an official visit to discuss bilateral military
ties and NATO expansion, the Interfax news agency said Sunday.
	   During his three-day stay, Sergeyev will meet with senior
Belgian defense officials and visit a number of military sites.
	   His agenda includes talks on interaction within the permanent
Russia-NATO Council, joint European security systems, NATO's
eastward expansion and Russia's participation in the Partnership
for Peace program, the news agency said.
	   (jai)
