<SLUG> BC-Weather Summary,1071 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands from
the National Weather Service.
	   Look for partly cloudy skies across our islands this afternoon
with a moderate east-southeast breeze. Increasing afternoon
cloudiness will be seen across the interior, west and northwest
parts of Puerto Rico, where widely scattered thunderstorms and a
few showers will develop by 3 p.m.
	   Only isolated showers are expected across the Virgin Islands.
However, in contrast to recent days, the area of coverage of this
rainfall will be less this afternoon.
	   Due to the unstable nature of the atmosphere today, these
thunderstorms will still produce two to three inches of rain, which
will cause brief flooding of urban and low lying areas.
	   Winds have increased across the local Caribbean waters since
Saturday morning and may gust to near 20 knots across the offshore
waters, with seas 4 to 5 feet.
	   Otherwise, typical summertime marine conditions are expected
across the region this afternoon and tonight.
	   San Juan and the northern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Partly sunny in the morning. Variably cloudy in the
afternoon with scattered showers. Isolated thunderstorms in the
west. High around 90. Wind east at 10 to 15 mph except northeast
along the coast. Chance of rain is 40 percent.
	   Tonight... Becoming partly cloudy in the east with isolated
showers. Fair skies in the west. Low 70 to 80. Light east wind.
Chance of rain less than 20 percent.
	   Monday... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers and
thunderstorms. High around 90. Wind east 10 to 15 mph except
northeast along the coast.
	   Eastern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers and
thunderstorms. High around 75 in the mountains, 85 to 90 in lower
elevations. Wind southeast at 10 to 15 mph.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy with widely scattered showers. Isolated
thunderstorms. Low of 65 in the mountains, 75 to 80 on the coasts.
Wind southeast 5 to 10 mph. Chance of rain is 20 percent.
	   Monday... Partly cloudy with a 20 percent chance of showers.
High around 75 in the mountains, 85 to 90 on the coasts. Wind east
at 10 to 15 mph.
	   Ponce and the southern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Mostly sunny in the morning. Partly cloudy in the
afternoon with scattered showers. Isolated afternoon thunderstorms
in the west. High 80 to 90. Wind southeast 10 to 15 mph. Chance of
rain is 30 percent.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy in the east with widely scattered
showers. Fair skies in the west. Low around 65 in the interior, 75
to 80 on the coasts. Chance of rain is 20 percent. Light east wind.
	   Monday... Partly cloudy with a 20 percent chance of showers and
afternoon thunderstorms. High 80 to 90. Southeast wind 10 to 15
mph.
	   Mayaguez and the western sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Sunny in the morning. Becoming variably cloudy in the
afternoon with scattered showers and isolated thunderstorms. High
85 to 90. Wind east 10 to 15 mph except for an afternoon sea breeze
along the west coast. Chance of rain is 50 percent.
	   Tonight... Variably cloudy in the evening with showers ending,
becoming mostly fair by midnight. Low 65 to 75. Light southeast
wind. Chance of rain is 20 percent.
	   Monday... Mostly sunny in the morning. Becoming variably cloudy
in the afternoon with a 30 percent chance of showers and
thunderstorms. High 85 to 90. Wind east 10 to 15 mph except for an
afternoon sea breeze along the west coast.
	   Interior sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Mostly sunny morning. Becoming variably cloudy in the
afternoon with a 50 percent chance of showers and thunderstorms.
High around 75 in the mountains, 85 to 90 in lower valleys. Wind
southeast at 10 to 15 mph.
	   Tonight... Becoming partly cloudy in the east with isolated
showers overnight. Fair skies in the west. Low around 70 on
mountain peaks, around 80 in lower valleys. Wind southeast around
10 mph. Chance of rain is 20 percent.
	   Monday... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers and
thunderstorms. High around 75 on mountain peaks, 85 to 90 in lower
valleys. East wind 10 to 15 mph.
	   St. Thomas, St. John and the Adjacent Islands-St. Croix:
	   Today... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers.
Slight chance of a thunderstorm. High 90 to 95. Wind southeast 10
to 15 mph.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers.
Low 75 to 80. Wind southeast around 10 mph.
	   Monday... Partly cloudy with a 20 percent chance of showers and
thunderstorms. High 90 to 95. Wind southeast 10 to 15 mph.
	   Atlantic waters north and northeast of Puerto Rico and the U.S.
Virgin Islands:
	   This afternoon... Wind east to southeast 10 to 15 kt. Seas 2 to
4 ft. Widely scattered showers. Wind and seas higher and visibility
below 1 nm near isolated thunderstorms northwest waters.
	   Tonight... Wind east to southeast 10 to 15 kt. Seas 2 to 3 ft.
Widely scattered showers. Isolated evening thunderstorms.
	   Monday... Wind east near 15 kt. Seas 2 to 4 ft. Widely scattered
showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Caribbean waters south and southeast of Puerto Rico and the U.S.
Virgin Islands:
	   This afternoon... Wind east to southeast around 15 kt. Seas 3 to
4 ft. Isolated showers.
	   Tonight... Wind east to southeast 10 to 15 kt. Seas 2 to 4 ft.
Isolated showers.
	   Monday... Wind east around 15 kt. Seas 3 to 4 ft. Widely
scattered showers.
	   Near shore waters of western Puerto Rico:
	   This afternoon... Wind variable, mainly southeast at 5 to 15 kt.
Seas 2 ft or less. Widely scattered showers. Wind and seas higher
near isolated thunderstorms.
	   Tonight... Wind east to southeast 10 to 15 kt. Seas 2 ft or
less. Isolated showers.
	   Monday... Wind east 10 to 15 kt. Seas 2 to 3 ft. Isolated
afternoon showers and thunderstorms.
	   Outlook for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands waters:
	   Monday night through Thursday... High pressure ridge from east
central Atlantic to Bahamas will remain nearly stationary. Wind
east to southeast at 20 kt or less. Seas less than 5 ft.
</TEXT>
