<HEADLINE>
Kenyan Martin Ojuku wins Stockholm Marathon
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   STOCKHOLM, Sweden (AP) _ Kenya's 25-year-old Martin Ojuku won
the Stockholm Marathon Sunday, finishing the 26.2 miles (42.2
kilometers) in 2 hours 16 minutes 12 seconds.
	   Ojuku held off Swede Anders Szalkai, who finished second in
2:16:33. Tanzanian Alfred Shemweta was third in 2:16:54 followed by
Kenyan John Mutai-Kipyator (2:18:43) and Norwegian Terje Naess
(2:19:29).
	   Norwegian favorite Grete Kirkeberg won the women's division in
2:37:O9. It was the 34-year old's third Stockholm Marathon victory.
	   More than 13,000 runners from 48 countries were registred for
the race, which was run in mild weather conditions (22C/71F).
	   (re/scw)	   
