	   JAKARTA (JP): State electricity company PLN has announced new
payment locations for its customers in the Jatinegara district and
its surrounding areas, effective this month.
	   ``We have introduced several new locations for bill payment to
replace the old locations which were ruined and burned during the
recent rioting,'' Tunggono, head of PLN's distribution office for
Jakarta and Tangerang, said in a statement Thursday.
	   Customers who formerly paid their bills at the Bank Central Asia
branch office on Jl. Jatinegara can now use the Bali Mester
subdistrict office, he said.
	   Those who used the BCA branches on Jl. Kalimalang and Jl. Dr.
Saharjo can pay their bills at PLN's branch office on Jl.
Jatinegara Timur and the former Manggarai Selatan subdistrict
office respectively.
	   Former users of the Bank Central Dagang branch office on Jl.
Gusti Ngurah Rai can pay at PLN's branch office on Jl. Jatinegara
Timur. (jsk)
	   
