<HEADLINE>
Algerian seeks political asylum in Spain
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MADRID, Spain (AP) _ An Algerian has asked Spain for political
asylum after fleeing his country with a military helicopter Sunday,
the Foreign Ministry said.
	   The Algerian, whose name was not released by the Ministry, filed
his request on Sunday after landing in the Mediterranean tourist
resort island of Ibiza. His petition will be reviewed by the
Ministry of Interior in the next few months, Joaquin Perez
Villanueva, a foreign ministry spokesman.
	   Perez said he could not give more details because asylum
petitions are confidential. Spain would return the helicopter, he
said. 	   
