	   JAKARTA (JP): Japanese Finance Minister Hikaru Matsunaga said
yesterday the Japanese government welcomed the foreign debt
rescheduling deal signed by Indonesia and international banks
Thursday.
	   ``We highly welcome this agreement which would help Indonesia
restore confidence of international markets in her economy and
currency,'' Matsunaga said in a statement sent by the Indonesian
office of Coordinating Minister for Economy, Finance and Industry.
	   ``As this agreement was achieved through the intensive
discussions of both parties, we would like to pay our best respects
to them for their efforts,'' the statement said.
	   ``We will continue to extend utmost assistance to Indonesia in
close cooperation with the international institutions including the
International Monetary Fund, as well as the G-7 and other
countries.
	   ``We hope the government of Indonesia will carry out the
economic reform effort steadily.''
	   
