<HEADLINE>
BM-Alcem/6.5 Alcem Posts P2.8-B Income, BUSINESS DAILY
</HEADLINE>
BM-Alcem/6.5 Alcem Posts P2.8-B Income, BUSINESS DAILY &QL; 
   June 05, 1998
   BUSINESS DAILY
   PHILIPPINES
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   Alsons Cement Corp. (Alcem), the construction arm of Alsons
Consolidated Resources (ACR), posted a 22% increase in its
consolidated sales from P2.3 billion in 1996 to P2.8 billion last
year. This was reported by Alcem officials during the firm's annual
stockholders meeting held recently at the Shangri-La Hotel in
Makati.
	   ``The past year established new milestones for Alcem on the road
toward its singular vision and strategic intent to become a
dominant cement and construction products manufacturer in the
Southeast Asian region,'' Alcem President Tomas I. Alcantara said.
	   Alcem's increase in consolidated sales, according to Alcantara,
came from a 16% increase in cement sales volume, ending last year
with total sales of 1.4 million metric tons (MT). ``The resulting
net income contribution to ACR by Alcem and its subsidiaries was
P225.2 million, or 34% of total net income,'' headded.
	   Citing another achievement, Alcantara reported that last year,
``the company registered the highest levels for both clinker and
cement production in its entire corporate history.'' The firm's
cement facilities at Lugait, Misamis Oriental and Iligan, Lanao del
Norte surpassed their performance in 1996 as their total clinker
production went up by 17% to 1,078, 940 MT, and their cement
production likewise increased by 17% with a total of 1,438,793 MT.
	   The Alcem president also cited the expansion in dealership
network of affiliate Market Developers Inc. which is mainly engaged
in the marketing and distribution of construction products,
industrial equipment and agricultural machinery. ``From 604 dealers
in 1996, we currently have 946 dealers, 245 of which are located in
Luzon,'' he pointed out.
	   ''MADE will mark its strengthened entry to the Luzon market to
handle principally cement distribution in its effort to be the
leading distribution of construction-related materials,'' he said.
	   Alcem continued to diversity into cement-related products
through its subsidiary Alsons Construction Chemicals Inc. (Alchem),
which engaged in the production of 282,323 liters of cement
admixtures and grinding aids last year.
	   Products introduced by Alcem include plasticizers,
superplasticizers and retarders. These products reduce the
water-cement ratio thereby enhancing concrete performance and
workability.
	   According to Alcantara, while the past year was another record
year for operations, Alcem was looking forward to several major
events and prospects in 1998.
	   ``Our expansion plant project in Lugait, Misamis Oriental, the
flagship of our expansionary thrust, will commence operations in
the second half of the year and will serve the bigger market of
Luzon. This presents new opportunities and challenges for us,'' he
pointed out.
	   Elected to Alcem's new board of directors at the stockholder's
meeting were ACR Chair and President Nicasio I. Alcantara; C.
Alcantara and Sons Inc.
	   (CASI) President Editha I. Alcantara; Alcem President Tomas I.
Alcantara; ``Holderbank'' Financiere Glaris Ltd. Executive
Committee Member Urs Bieri; PIA Holdings Chair and CEO Alfred
Schmidt; Sycip Salazar Hernandez and Gatmaitan Law Offices Managing
Partner Andres G. Gatmaitan; and Philippine Tobacco Flue-Curing and
Redrying Corp. Director and Treasurer Bienvenido A.
	   Tan III.
	   Alcem, a publicly-listed firm in the Philippine Stock Exchange,
is the country's second largest cement manufacturer.
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 BUSINESS DAILY all rights reserved as distributed
by WorldSources, Inc. 	   
