<HEADLINE>
Police arrest ravers on drug charges
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ATHENS, Greece (AP) _ Police on Sunday arrested 11 people on
drug charges after an all-night rave party on the island of Evia,
about 60 kilometers (37.5 miles) northeast of Athens, media reports
said.
	   An early morning routine police patrol around the wooded area of
Steni on Evia came across people allegedly leaving a rave party in
the area attended by around 300 people. Eleven people were arrested
after they were found to be in possession of small quantities of
heroin, marijuana, cocaine and ecstasy pills, local media said.
	   (eb)	   
