<HEADLINE>
Admirals beat Claymores 26-23
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   EDINBURGH, Scotland (AP) _ Kurt Warner threw two touchdown
passes including the winner with 1:51 to play as the Amsterdam
Admirals defeated the Scottish Claymores 26-23 Sunday in the
season-ending NFL Europe game for both teams.
	   Trailing 23-20, Warner hit Juan Daniels with a 17-yard pass to
seal the victory. The Admirals finished 7-3 and the Claymores ended
2-8.
	   The Frankfurt Galaxy and Rhein Fire of Dusseldorf also finished
7-3 and will play each other on June 14 in the World Bowl in
Frankfurt, the championship game of NFL Europe.
	   The Admirals missed out because of a poorer record in
head-to-head games against the two German teams.
	   Warner, allocated from the St. Louis Rams, put the Admirals
ahead 7-0 with a 4-yard pass to Frank Temming with 7:02 left in the
first quarter.
	   The Claymores tied on a 3-yard run by J.J. Smith late in the
quarter, and then led at halftime on 40-yard, second-half field
goal by Jon Baker. Baker is allocated from the Miami Dolphins.
	   The Admirals went back ahead 13-10 on Malcolm Thomas's 4-yard
run in the third quarter, setting the stage for the wide-open final
quarter before a crowd of 8,762.
	   The Claymores Kory Blackwell returned an intercepted pass from
Warner 29 yards to give the Claymores a 17-13 lead. But the
Admirals Ralph Dawkins scored on a 10-yard to make it 20-17.
	   The Claymores then got a 42-yard field from Baker with 4:40 left
_ and a 30-yarder by Parker with 3:27 to play, to lead 23-20 and
set up Warner's winning pass.
	   Warner hit 12 of 29 for 187 yards with one interception and two
touchdowns.
	   (scw)	   
