<HEADLINE>
Germany army evacuates Europeans from Eritrea
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BONN, Germany (AP) _ A German military aircraft carrying 217
Europeans evacuated from Eritrea landed in Cologne on Sunday.
	   The Airbus took off from the Eritrean capital Asmara at 6:30
p.m. Saturday without incident and made a stopover in Jeddah, Saudi
Arabia.
	   The plane carried 94 Germans and 77 Dutch. The other passengers
came from Sweden, Denmark, France, Italy, Spain, Switzerland and
Belgium.
	   Defense Minister Volker Ruehe commended the army's success.
	   (aet-cb)	   
