<SLUG> DSE-INDEX-UP-BY-81.21 sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DSE index up by 81.21 ptson heavy buying spree, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
DSE index up by 81.21 ptson heavy buying spree, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 07, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
   Economic ReporterASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   The trading at Dhaka Stock Exchange (DSE) witnessed a bullish
trend yesterday with significant rise in the All Share Price Index
as well as the turnover.
	   On a heavy buying spree, ahead of the national budget to be
announced on June 10, the index rose by 81.21 points or 11 per cent
to 778.41 from previous day's close at 697.20.
	   With the hope that the forthcoming budget would contain some
incentives to boost the country's capital market, the small
investors seemed to be more confident to inject their money in
recent days, a market expert opined.
	   ``The trading at the DSE improves at the news that the
government will reduce corporate tax for listed companies from
current tax rate of 35 per cent,'' he said .
	   On the day, shares of 149 listed securities were transacted with
141 in gains, seven in loss ,while one remained unchanged.
	   Some 663,380 shares and debentures valued at Tk 7.78 crore
changed hands on the day against 734,657 shares and debentures
worth Tk 7.52 crore on the previous day.
	   Chick Tex (116,500), Quasem Drycells (55,600), Shinepukur
Holdings (37,850), Ashraf Textiles (29,000), Eagle Star Textiles
(22,450), Dynamic Textiles (21,540), Beximco Pharma (28,900),
Beximco Synthetic (20,080) and Rose Heaven Ball Pen (46,000) were
among the volume leaders.
	   The major gainers included IDLC (Tk 127.34), Aziz Pipes (Tk
102.60), Singer Bangladesh (Tk 270.42), National Tubes (Tk 113.42),
Aman Sea Food (Tk 124.25) and Apex Foods (Tk 138.97).
	   There were no significant losers yesterday except Beximco Tex
(Tk 62.00).
	   Market capitalisation on the day stood at Tk 70.01 billion
equivalent to US dollar 1.51 billion at the close of the
yesterday's trading against previous day's close at Tk 62.70
billion or US dollar 1.35 billion.
	   
</TEXT>
