<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-World Cup-Torricelli,0222 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Juventus defender may be axed because of ankle injury
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; With Sports-Soccer-World Cup-Italy &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   SENLIS, France (AP) _ Defender Moreno Torricelli may be cut from
Italy's World Cup team because of an injured right ankle and
possibly replaced by striker Enrico Chiesa, coach Cesare Maldini
said Sunday.
	   A final decision about Torricelli's exclusion will be made
Monday following a another series of examinations.
	   Torricelli, 28, of Italian league champion Juventus, has been
sidelined the last seven days because of a sore ankle and did not
play the warmups against Sweden on Tuesday nor against a French
regional selection on Sunday.
	   The defender was not expected to be in the starting lineup
Thursday in Italy's Group B opener against Chile.
	   Chiesa, of Parma, already is with the Italian team. He was
brough to France as a possible replacement for Alessandro Del
Piero, who's recovering from a right thigh strain and is expected
to stay with the team.
	   Chiesa's possible inclusion would raise to five the number of
Italy's strikers and reduce defenders to six.
	   The final lists of 22 World Cup players have been submitted to
FIFA by the June 2 deadline but the teams still can replace injured
players until June 10.
</TEXT>
