	   Foreign Minister Abdus Samad Azad yesterday sought all-out
support of the Lions club members in implementing programmes for
the economic emancipation of the people so that the political
independence becomes meaningful, reports BSS.
	   The minister was inaugurating the 11th annual multiple district
convention 98 of the Multiple District 315, Bangladesh, of the
Lions clubs international here.
	   Council chairman Lion Syed Nasir Husain presided over the
convention while immediate past council chairman Lion Sheikh Kabir
Hussain, Lion Muslim Ali Khan, Lion ABM Firoz and Lion Shafiqul
Islam Khan spoke.
	   The Foreign Minister said the main objective of the present
government is to bring about economic emancipation of the people.
''We want to free the people from the shackles of poverty, and we
are working relentlessly towards this end,'' he told the Lions.
	   He asked them to expand their welfare-oriented programmes and
come up with some poverty-eradication schemes to help lift people
from below the poverty line. He commended the pro-people programmes
of the Lions clubs and wished success of the convention.
	   Lion Syed Nasir informed that a total of 8,000 Lions were
working in six sub-districts under 300 clubs across the country to
serve the people.
	   Lion Sheikh Kabir said that Lions clubs would involve themselves
in poverty eradication and vocational training programmes to help
support the poorer section getting self-employment.
	   
