	   The government will distribute rice free of cost among the poor
and destitute people in union levels for four months from the next
year.
	   ``The government has taken the step for the welfare of the poor
people,'' said State Minister for Disaster Management and Relief
Talukdar Abdul Khaleq here on Friday.
	   Addressing the annual conference of Relief and Rehabilitation
Employees Association, he informed that for the project vulnerable
group feeding cards will be distributed in every union.
	   He told the function, apart from building infrastructure, the
government has taken up the programme to distribute free of cost
rice through VGF cards in the natural disaster affected areas.
	   ``From the next year the programme of distributing free rice for
four months will be extended all over the country,'' he added.
	   Association president and plaintiff in Bangabandhu murder case,
AFM Mohitul Islam presided over the conference, said an official
handout.
	   
