<SLUG> DEED-WRITERS-URGE-GOVT sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Deed writers urge govt to meet 6-pt demand by June 13, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
Deed writers urge govt to meet 6-pt demand by June 13, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 07, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
   Staff ReporterASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   The deed writers of the country called upon the government to
realise their 6-point demand by June 13 next, otherwise they will
go for indefinite strike throughout the country.
	   The call was made at a press conference of the Bangladesh Deed
Writers Association held at the Registration Complex in the city
yesterday afternoon.
	   The written statement of the association read out by Mukter
Hossain, Organising Secretary, said that a total of two lakh deed
writers and stamp vendors are working in the country.
	   The government, following publishing of DOLA (Department of Land
Administration) Report which stressed the need for modernising the
registration system of the country, has been trying to implement
the recommendations of the report reportedly to unemploy the deed
writers and vendors, the association leaders said.
	   The leaders also called for cancelling the DOLA Report saying
that it would create a lot of problems in selling and buying the
land for which the country would lose a good amount of revenue from
the registration of land. At present, the government earns taka 900
crore from the registration.
	   The 6-point demand of the association includes cancellation of
DOLA Report, continuing of present stamp-vendor deeds, cancellation
of form system, formation of deed writers council, building of
office for vendors at every sub-registrar office and offering 10
per cent commission to the stamp vendors for selling the same.
	   The press conference was attended, among others, by Elahi Box
Mondol, President of the association, Abdur Rouf, Secretary
General, Salim Reza, Vice President, Faridul Islam Bahadur, Awlad
Hossain and others.
	   
</TEXT>
