	   Leaders of the Bangladesh Federal Union of Journalists (BFUJ)
and Dhaka Union of Journalists (DUJ) yesterday expressed
indignation over the closure of the office of daily Reporter
without prior notice.
	   In a joint statement BFUJ President Amanullah Kabir, Secretary
General MA Aziz, Acting President of DUJ Abu Saleh and General
Secretary Ruhul Amin Gazi alleged that the Editor and Director of
the daily Ershad Mazumdar has kept the office under lock and key
since June 4.
	   They also alleged that the office was closed with an ill motive
to deprive the journalists of their dues and legitimate claims.
	   The BFUJ and DUJ leaders condemned such a step and demanded of
the person concerned to resolve the problems with the journalists
and employees by immediately reopening of the office of the daily.
	   
