<SLUG> BC-Egypt-Eritrean Diplomats </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Eritrean diplomats flee Ethiopia
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   CAIRO, Egypt (AP) _ A group of Eritrean diplomats and their
families arrived in Cairo Sunday from Ethiopia, saying Ethiopian
authorities refused to let them carry anything more than their hand
bags.
	   Border tensions between the two African nations gained
international attention after Ethiopian jets bombed an airport near
the Eritrean capital of Asmara on Saturday.
	   With rising possibility of a war, Eritrea ordered its diplomats
to evacuate their posts in the Ethiopian capital of Addis Ababa and
the city of Mekele, and a group of 57 Eritreans arrived in Cairo
from Addis Ababa aboard the Egyptian carrier Egyptair.
	   The diplomats said Ethiopian authorities allowed them to leave
with only hand bags. The Eritreans are currently being held in
Cairo airport's quarantine section pending clearance by the Health
Ministry.
	   The diplomats and their families are expected to return to
Asmara.
	   Egyptair on Sunday announced it is resuming flights to Addis
Ababa after Ethiopian aviation officials informed them their routes
and airport were secure.
