<HEADLINE>
9 killed, 16 injured in road accident in eastern Egypt
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   CAIRO, Egypt (AP) _ A station wagon taxi collided with a bus in
an Egyptian port city Sunday, killing nine people in the taxi and
injuring 16 in the bus, Egypt's Middle East News Agency said.
	   The accident happened on a main street in Ismailiya when the
taxi overtook a car and swerved into the wrong lane into the path
of an oncoming bus, MENA said.
	   It said the taxi driver was killed along with his eight
passengers. The driver and 15 passengers of the bus were injured.
	   Ismailiya is 100 kilometers (67 miles) east of Cairo.
