<SLUG> BC-Argentina-Russia-Zyuganov,0224 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Russian Communist leader says chaos is in the offing in his
</HEADLINE>
country &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   BUENOS AIRES, Argentina (AP) _ The leader of the Communist Party
of the Russian Federation said Sunday that President Boris Yeltsin
has installed in his country ``a feudal mafia,'' following the
disappearance of the Soviet Union.
	   ``In my country, nobody is building capitalism. We are victims
of the constant robbery and looting of our national resources''
Gennady Zyuganov said at a press conference in the central
headquarters of the Argentine Communist Party.
	   He predicted ``a chaotic situation if Yeltsin sticks to his
present economic model.''
	   According to Zyuganov, 20 million people are now unemployed in
Russia ``and another 15 million are leading a miserable life.''
	   Zyuganov said he intends to reinforce links with Latin American
leftist organizations. He arrived Saturday from Brazil and is
scheduled to fly Sunday night to Cuba for a two-day visit.
	   ``In the case of Cuba, our relations have been very strong for a
long time, and we plan to strengthen them'', he said.
	   Zyuganov depicted the current United States economic blockade
against Cuba as ``a political anachronism'' and praised the Cuban
people ``for being able to reform their system without sacrifying
its social achievements.'' 	   
</TEXT>
