<SLUG> BC-Egypt-Eritrean Diplomats,0171 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Eritrean diplomats flee Ethiopia
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   CAIRO, Egypt (AP) _ A group of Eritrean diplomats and their
families arrived Sunday in Cairo from Ethiopia, saying Ethiopian
authorities refused to let them carry anything more than their hand
bags.
	   Border tensions between the two Horn of Africa nations escalated
after Ethiopian jets bombed an airport near the Eritrean capital of
Asmara on Saturday.
	   With rising possibility of a war, Eritrea ordered its diplomats
to evacuate their posts in the Ethiopian capital of Addis Ababa and
the city of Mekele. A group of 57 Eritreans arrived in Cairo from
Addis Ababa aboard the Egyptian carrier Egyptair.
	   The Eritreans were being held in Cairo airport's quarantine
section pending clearance by the Health Ministry. The diplomats and
their families are expected to return to Asmara.
	   Egyptair on Sunday announced that it was resuming flights to
Addis Ababa after Ethiopian aviation officials informed them their
routes and airport were secure. 	   
