<SLUG> BC-Colombia-Drug Boss, 1st Ld,0160 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Police capture reputed head of Caribbean cartel
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: CORRECTS to orlandex sted Gamboa in graf 3 &QL; 
 &UR; By FRANK BAJAK &QC; 
 &UR; Associates Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   BOGOTA, Colombia (AP) _ One of Colombia's last remaining major
drug bosses has been captured in the northern port of Barranquilla,
his appearance altered by hair implants and his pockets full of
cash, the deputy national police director announced Sunday.
	   Caribbean cartel leader Alberto Orlandez Gamboa, alias ``The
Snail,'' allegedly smuggled tons of cocaine to Europe and the
United States since 1991. He has been indicted in Miami federal
court on charges of drug trafficking and money laundering, said the
police official, Gen. Luis Ernesto Gilibert.
	   He said Colombia's foreign ministry would decide whether to
extradite Orlandez for trial to the United States under last year's
law that reinstated extradition.
	   The 43-year-old Orlandez, 4th graf pvs.
</TEXT>
