<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Brazil-Cruz Hurt,0165 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Brazilian defender hurt, misses practice
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   OZOIR-LA-FERRIERE, France (AP) _ Brazilian defender Andre Cruz
sat out Sunday's practice with a sore thigh muscle but it probably
wasn't a serious injury.
	   ``Yesterday I was fine, and this morning I had a pain in the
back of my thigh. That would worry anybody,'' said Cruz, a reserve
for starting fullback Aldair.
	   Cruz said the results of MRI test Sunday were negative.
	   ``There was no swelling, no lesion, no nothing,'' he said.
``I'll treat it with massages and take it day-to-day.''
	   Cruz, 29, plays for AC Milan in Italy's first division. After a
long recuperation from a leg injury, he was left off Brazil's World
Cup squad but later summoned to replace the injured Marcio Santos.
	   A leg injury also was the reason that star striker Romario was
cut from the team last week.
	   Brazil opens the Cup on Wednesday against Scotland.
</TEXT>
