<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Football-Dragons-Monarchs,0258 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Monarchs 28, Dragons 20
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BARCELONA, Spain (AP) _ Backup quarterback Wally Richardson
passed for two touchdowns and 165 yards to lead the England
Monarchs over the Barcelona Dragons 28-20 Sunday, in the
season-ending NFL Europe game for both teams.
	   England held a one-point margin going into the fourth quarter,
when Don Silvestri kicked a 51-yard field goal and Rob Hart added
another of 31 yards to seal their victory. The Monarchs finished
the season 3-7, while the Dragons ended 4-6.
	   England led 14-0 at the end of the first quarter, with starter
George LaRocca connecting on a 15-yard touchdown pass to Reggie
Jones and Richardson, who took over when LaRocca was injured,
completing a 31-yard touchdown pass to Alan Allen.
	   Barcelona roared back in the second quarter. Jim Ritchey threw
touchdown passes of 22 and 10 yards each to Marco Martos, and Jesus
Angoy kicked a field goal to give the Dragons a 17-14 halftime
lead.
	   Richardson put England on top for good with a 24-yard touchdown
pass to Shawn Turner with 8:17 in the third quarter.
	   After Angoy trimmed the lead to 21-20 on a 41-yard field goal
with 45 seconds to go in the quarter, Silvestri and Hart replied
with a pair of their own _ with 3:16 and 1:45 left respectively in
the fourth quarter. Silvestri's field goal was worth four points
because it was longer than 50 yards.
	   Richardson completed 12 of 24 passes, while Ritchey connected on
16 of 36 passes for 166 yds. Ritchey was sacked six times.
</TEXT>
