<TEXT>
	   WORLD AT 0000 GMT:
	   NEW:
	   _ANALYSIS-HORN OF AFRICA CONFLICT. Conflict shows leaders follow
own agenda.
	   _MEXICO-REBELS. Mexican army clashes with rebels.
	   _US-SHUTTLE-MIR. Discovery is getting ready to undock from Mir.
	   _GERMANY-RUSSIA. Yeltsin meets Kohl in Germany.
	   _US-TONY AWARDS. A battle of big, corporate-produced musicals.
	   _BRITAIN-LINDA MCCARTNEY. Paul McCartney will speak at memorial.
	   _ISRAEL-SOLOMON DEBATE. Debate over King Solomon's role as
builder.
 &UR; MAIN SPOT NEWS:
	   ASMARA, Eritrea _ Diplomatic efforts are under way to prevent
the border conflict between Eritrea and Ethiopia from exploding
into full-scale war, with officials hoping that Monday's summit of
African leaders will produce new ideas for a settlement.
ERITREA-ETHIOPIA. Recap expected by 0300 GMT. By Karin Davies. AP
Photos ASM101,104,120,123.
	   ALSO:
	   _ANALYSIS-HORN OF AFRICA CONFLICT _ Ethiopia-Eritrea conflict
shows regional leaders follow their own agenda. Expected by 0300
GMT.
	   PRISTINA, Yugoslavia _ Serb forces press their campaign against
separatist rebels in the Kosovo countryside, while police swinging
clubs beat protesters at an independence rally in the provincial
capital. YUGOSLAVIA-KOSOVO. Recap expected by 0200 GMT. By Ismet
Hajdari. AP Photos PRI101.
	   ALSO MOVED:
	   _ALBANIA-REFUGEE CHILDREN _ Kosovo children survive trek to
Albania alone.
	   _US-YUGOSLAVIA-KOSOVO _ U.S. senator urges action to end
fighting in Kosovo.
	   PARIS _ Striking Air France pilots offer to work for free to fly
foreign fans to the World Cup, but their walkout shows no sign of
ending Monday as it enters its second week. AIR FRANCE-STRIKE.
Recap expected by 0300 GMT. By Deborah Seward. AP photos
PAR104-105,107-109.
	   MEXICO CITY _ Rebels open fire on an army patrol in western
Mexico, and 11 people die in a subsequent shootout, the military
says. MEXICO-REBELS. Has moved. By Niko Price.
	   SPACE CENTER, Houston _ The space shuttle Discovery is scheduled
to undock Monday after four days of joint flight, bringing home the
last American to live on Mir, as well as several thousand kilograms
(pounds) of Russian gear. US-SHUTTLE-MIR. Expected by 0100 GMT;
undocking scheduled about 1600 GMT. By Marcia Dunn. AP Photos
XHTN101-102.
	   NEW YORK _ It's a battle of big musicals created by big
corporations: Disney's ``The Lion King'' and Livent's ``Ragtime''
are vying for the best musical prize as the Tony Awards honor the
1997-98 Broadway season. US-TONY AWARDS. Developing, ceremony
begins at 0000 GMT, first lead expected by 0035 GMT, a wrap-up and
complete list of winners by 0330 GMT. By Michael Kuchwara. AP
Photos planned.
	   LONDON _ To the strains of ``Let It Be,'' Paul McCartney will on
Monday say a public farewell to his wife, Linda, at a memorial
service. BRITAIN-LINDA MCCARTNEY. Developing, memorial service
scheduled for 8:30 p.m. (1930 GMT). By Sue Leeman.
	   WASHINGTON _ Weeks after India and Pakistan triggered nuclear
fears in a jittery world, a major U.S. ally in Asia is in the
United States with worries about a nation whose nuclear ambitions
created a military crisis four years ago _ North Korea. US-KOREA.
Has moved. By Robert Burns.
	   BONN, Germany _ The Russian president travels Monday to key
trading partner Germany following a financial crisis at home, but
Boris Yeltsin says he won't come begging for aid. GERMANY-RUSSIA.
Expected by 0200 GMT; Yeltsin's arrival scheduled for 1500 GMT.
	   FAISABAD, Afghanistan _ Aid workers are trying to assess whether
serious disease has broken out in remote villages of northern
Afghanistan devastated during last weekend's earthquake.
AFGHANISTAN-QUAKE. Has moved. By Judith Ingram.
	   LONDON _ International airline pilots have listed 150 airports
with major safety problems and singled out 15 _ including San
Francisco, Nice and Hong Kong, _ which they believe are
``critically deficient,'' according to a newspaper report. DANGER
AIRPORTS. Has moved.
	   BEIRUT, Lebanon _ Lebanon's first municipal elections in 35
years became a referendum Sunday on Christian-Muslim coexistence in
Beirut and a fight for the leadership of Shiite Muslims in southern
Lebanon. LEBANON-ELECTIONS. Has moved. By Sam F. Ghattas. AP Photos
BEI101,103.
	   ALSO MOVED:
	   _LEBANON-FRONT-LINE VOTE _ Municipal vote seen part of fight
against Israeli occupation.
	   JERUSALEM _ Was King Solomon the great builder of ancient
Israel, as has long been held _ or was the architect actually
someone less well-known? The debate is gripping modern Israel.
ISRAEL-SOLOMON DEBATE. Expected by 0100 GMT. By Nicolas B. Tatro.
	   RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil _ An Amazon tribe living beyond the reach
of modern society, has been discovered by federal Indian agents
near the border with Peru. BRAZIL-NEW AMAZON TRIBE. Has moved. By
Jack Epstein.
	   LOOKING AHEAD: South Korean President Kim Dae-jung makes a state
visit to Washington on Tuesday. The World Cup begins in France on
Wednesday.
