<HEADLINE>
Mahathir's daughter weds Indonesian lensman
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: CORRECTS age in 4th graf &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) _ Marina Mahathir, the eldest
daughter of Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad, has married
an Indonesian photographer, news reports said Monday.
	   Sunday's wedding of Marina and Tara Sosrowardoyo, 46, at
Mahathir's official residence, was announced by the prime
minister's press office, the official Bernama news agency said.
	   It was attended by family members of the bride and the groom,
said Press Secretary Zakaria Wahab.
	   Marina, 41, a well-known columnist who is often critical of
Malaysian government policies and society, has a 10-year-old
daughter from her first marriage.
	   Her first book, a collection of her columns entitled ``In
Liberal Doses,'' was released in November.
	   She is also involved in AIDS-awareness campaigns and is the
chairperson of the Malaysian Aids Foundation. 	   
