<HEADLINE>
URGENT
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Newspaper editor loyal to Cambodian leader Hun Sen shot

<TEXT>
	   PHNOM PENH, Cambodia (AP) _ The publisher-editor of the
country's most widely-read newspaper _ which supports Cambodian
strongman Hun Sen _ was shot by an unidentified gunman Monday, his
wife said.
	   At least two of six bullets fired struck Thong Uy Pang, 55,
while he was sitting on his motorcycle about 8:05 a.m. outside a
pagoda, Yim Phanny said from the capital's Calmette Hospital. Her
husband was being treated and his condition was unclear.
	   There was no immediate known motive for the shooting. Thong Uy
Phang's hard-hitting Koh Santepheap (Island of Peace) backs Hun
Sen, who has often been accused of orchestrating attacks on
journalists supporting his opponents.
	   Hun Sen is engaged in an election campaign seeking to restore
international legitimacy and aid lost since his bloody coup last
year against his co-prime minister, Prince Norodom Ranariddh.
	   The opposition has complained of being denied access to the
broadcast media, controlled entirely by Hun Sen. 	   
